# WHAT IT IS
#   rundler is Alchemy's open-source ERC-4337 (Account
#   Abstraction) bundler in Rust.  ERC-4337 lets Ethereum users
#   send "UserOperations" — pseudo-transactions that get
#   wrapped into a real transaction by a "bundler" — and a
#   bundler's job is to maintain a mempool of pending
#   UserOperations, simulate them against the deployed entry-
#   point contract, gas-price them, pack them into a single
#   EVM transaction, and submit it to the chain.  rundler
#   ships:
#     • the `node` subcommand — runs the full bundler in a
#       single process (Pool + Builder + Rpc colocated)
#     • `pool`, `builder`, `rpc` — each individual subsystem
#       as a standalone gRPC service for horizontal scale-out
#     • `backend` — combined Pool + Builder behind a gRPC
#       gateway (one-chain backend a gateway can connect to)
#     • `admin` — operator commands against a running bundler
#       (drain mempool, force-rebroadcast, inspect entries)
#
#   Built on alloy-rs (the modern Rust Ethereum primitives
#   stack) and observability-instrumented end-to-end via
#   opentelemetry-rust + OTLP/gRPC exporter, with structured
#   logging through `tracing-subscriber` + `tracing-opentelemetry`
#   so every span flows out as OTel telemetry that
#   Datadog / Honeycomb / Grafana Tempo / Jaeger / Lightstep
#   / NewRelic / SigNoz / Sentry / Tempo / Loki / Tempo / Zipkin /
#   Pyroscope / and any other OTLP-receiving collector can
#   consume verbatim.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from bin/rundler/src/cli/
#                       mod.rs `Cli` struct + `Command` enum +
#                       per-subcommand `*CliArgs` Args struct
#                       declarations, plus the flattened
#                       `CommonArgs`, `MetricsArgs`, `LogsArgs`
#                       groups extracted via `gh api repos/
#                       alchemyplatform/rundler/contents/bin/
#                       rundler/src/cli/...`)
#
#   rundler [GLOBAL OPTIONS] <SUBCOMMAND> [args...]
#
#   Global options  (CommonArgs — flattened into Cli, every
#                    subcommand sees them; all are also
#                    available via env-var equivalents):
#     --network <NAME>               Network preset (e.g.
#                                    ethereum, optimism, base,
#                                    arbitrum, polygon,
#                                    plus per-network testnets)
#                                    [env: NETWORK]
#     --chain_spec <PATH>            Chain spec file path
#                                    (overrides --network)
#     --node_http <URL>              ETH node HTTP URL to
#                                    connect to
#     --unsafe                       Turn unsafe bundling mode
#                                    on  [env: UNSAFE]
#     --max_verification_gas <N>     Max verification gas
#     (plus dozens of other tuning knobs: --max_call_gas,
#      --max_simulate_handle_ops_gas, --max_priority_fee_per_gas,
#      --min_unstake_delay, --min_stake_value, --bundle_priority_
#      fee_overhead_percent, --base_fee_accept_percent,
#      --priority_fee_mode_kind, --priority_fee_mode_value,
#      --vp_max_revert_reason_size, --max_user_ops_per_bundle,
#      --da_gas_oracle_type, --target_bundle_gas_limit,
#      --enabled_entry_points, --entry_point_v0_6_enabled,
#      --entry_point_v0_7_enabled, --aggregator_options, etc.)
#
#   MetricsArgs  (flattened):
#     --metrics.port <PORT>          Metrics server port
#     --metrics.host <HOST>          Metrics server host
#     --metrics.sample_interval_millis <N>
#     --metrics.tags <KEY=VAL>...    Repeatable metric tags
#     --metrics.buckets <CSV>        Histogram bucket spec
#
#   LogsArgs  (flattened):
#     --logs.json                    Emit logs as JSON
#     --logs.otlp_grpc_endpoint <URL>
#                                    Send tracing spans to OTLP
#                                    gRPC endpoint
#     --logs.otlp_service_name <NAME>
#                                    OpenTelemetry service.name
#                                    resource attribute
#     --logs.otlp_resource <KEY=VAL>...
#                                    Repeatable OTel resource
#                                    attributes
#
#   Subcommands:
#     node                           Run the full bundler in a
#                                    single process (Pool +
#                                    Builder + Rpc colocated)
#     rpc                            Run only the Rpc server
#                                    (connects to standalone
#                                    Pool + Builder gRPC
#                                    services)
#     pool                           Run only the Pool server
#                                    (UserOperation mempool +
#                                    simulation gRPC service)
#     builder                        Run only the Builder server
#                                    (pulls from Pool, packs
#                                    bundles, broadcasts gRPC
#                                    service)
#     backend                        Combined Pool + Builder
#                                    behind a gRPC gateway
#                                    (single-chain backend for
#                                    multi-chain gateway
#                                    deployments)
#     admin                          Operator commands against a
#                                    running bundler (drain
#                                    mempool, force-rebroadcast,
#                                    inspect entries)
#
#   Standard clap auto-flags:
#     -h, --help                     Show help (root + each
#                                    subcommand)
#     -V, --version                  Show version (0.11.0)
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   Direct dependency on `opentelemetry = "0.28.0"` +
#   `opentelemetry-otlp = "0.28.0"` (with `grpc-tonic` feature)
#   + `opentelemetry_sdk = "0.28.0"` + `tracing-opentelemetry =
#   "0.29.0"` declared in bin/rundler/Cargo.toml —
#   `opentelemetry-rust` is THE canonical Rust implementation
#   of the CNCF OpenTelemetry specification, maintained by the
#   OpenTelemetry community at the open-telemetry/
#   opentelemetry-rust repository (1,900+ stars; the
#   predominant typed Rust SDK for traces / metrics / logs that
#   every production Rust observability pipeline ends up
#   depending on — used by build-trust/ockam, deuxfleurs-org/
#   garage, firezone/firezone, numaproj/numaflow, alchemyplatform
#   /rundler, casualjim/dainty, biomejs/gritql, aembke/fred.rs,
#   and dozens of other production Rust applications that emit
#   OTLP telemetry).  opentelemetry-rust exposes the typed
#   `opentelemetry::global::tracer_provider()` /
#   `opentelemetry::global::set_tracer_provider(provider)` /
#   `opentelemetry::global::tracer("module.name")` /
#   `opentelemetry::global::meter("module.name")` /
#   `opentelemetry::global::logger_provider()` factories, the
#   typed `Tracer::span_builder(name).with_kind(SpanKind::Server
#   ).with_attributes(...).start(&tracer)` span constructor
#   chain, the typed `SpanContext` /  `SpanId` /  `TraceId` /
#   `TraceFlags` /  `TraceState` propagation primitives, the
#   typed `Context` carrier with `Context::current()` /
#   `Context::with_value(...)` / `cx.span()` accessors, the
#   typed `BoxedTracer` / `BoxedSpan` runtime polymorphism
#   layer for SDK swapping, every typed propagator (W3C
#   TraceContext, B3, Jaeger, Baggage), and the typed Resource
#   builder (`Resource::new(KeyValue::new("service.name",
#   "rundler"))`).  `opentelemetry_sdk` exposes the typed
#   `SdkTracerProvider::builder().with_resource(...).with_span_
#   processor(processor).with_sampler(sampler).build()`,
#   `SdkMeterProvider::builder().with_resource(...).with_reader(
#   reader).build()`, and `SdkLoggerProvider::builder()` SDK-
#   side configuration entry points.  `opentelemetry-otlp`
#   exposes the typed `SpanExporter::builder().with_tonic()
#   .with_endpoint(url).with_protocol(Protocol::Grpc).build()` /
#   `MetricExporter::builder().with_tonic()...` /
#   `LogExporter::builder().with_tonic()...` OTLP-protocol-
#   compliant exporters that round-trip with any OTLP-receiving
#   collector.  `tracing-opentelemetry` is the bridge that
#   makes `tracing::info_span!`, `tracing::error!`,
#   `tracing::span::Span::current()` flow into the OTel SDK
#   transparently.  rundler's `bin/rundler/src/cli/tracing.rs`
#   constructs a `SdkTracerProvider` per process boot, wires it
#   into `tracing-subscriber` via `tracing_opentelemetry::layer
#   ()`, and emits typed spans through the OTLP/gRPC exporter
#   for every UserOperation simulation, pool admission, bundle
#   build, signing, and RPC call.  Verified via:
#     gh api repos/alchemyplatform/rundler/contents/bin/
